HEADWORD: Killock
<hw>Kil"lock</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Scot.
<ets>killick</ets> ⟦ldquo⟧the flue [fluke] of an anchor.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Jamieson.</au>]</ety> <def>A small anchor; also, a kind of anchor
formed by a stone inclosed by pieces of wood fastened together.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>killick</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

